                        "displayName": "Wes McKinney",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/New_York"
                    },
                    "body": "It looks like the {{flags}} argument from {{PyObject_GetBuffer}} is being ignored. NumPy tries to get a mutable buffer, and if that fails (which it must if the buffer is readonly), then it sets WRITEABLE to false: https://github.com/numpy/numpy/blob/e8d177f74adbe5c7630721a4ab3f20f58839ac99/numpy/core/src/multiarray/ctors.c#L3711. Patch incoming",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=wesm",
                        "name": "wesm",
                        "key": "wesmckinn",
